{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation","step":0},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pastry","step":0},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Preheat oven to 220°C. Set aside a baking tray (30 x 40 cm).","step":1},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place flour and butter into mixing bowl and mix <b>3 sec\/speed 4<b>.","step":2},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Add water, lemon juice, salt and egg yolk and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer onto a floured work surface, shape into a ball, then flatten into a disc. Roll dough out between 2 sheets of baking paper into a circle (approx. 30 cm wide, 3 mm thickness), dusting pastry and rolling pin with flour and lifting pastry as needed. Transfer pastry with baking paper onto baking tray. Remove the top sheet of baking paper and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","step":3},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Filling","step":0},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place garlic, spring onions\/shallots and chives into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","step":4},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Add ricotta, sour cream, egg, pepper and salt and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>.","step":5},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Transfer mixture into centre of the reserved pastry, leaving a 5 cm border. Quickly lift border over the edge of the filling, pinching it slightly as you go (avoid pastry on pastry, make sure to lift your pastry over filling). Arrange half of the tomatoes on top of filling and season with extra salt and pepper. Brush pastry rim with beaten egg and bake for 20-22 minutes (220°C), until pastry is cooked and golden brown.","step":6},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Garnish with rocket, remaining tomatoes and pine nuts (optional), then drizzle with vino cotto to serve.","step":7}],"usefulItems":"baking paper, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), rolling pin, pastry brush, oven","id":"r254174","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-osAyEBwu34g\/XZVQg5sU3II\/AAAAAAAAdCI\/N59z-VCTy_0w